# CSS & SCSS Styling Guidelines

## Architecture Overview
The project uses a hybrid approach with Tailwind CSS and custom SCSS:

### Main Styles
- Global CSS: [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css)
- Main SCSS: [src/scss/main.scss](mdc:src/scss/main.scss)
- Tailwind config: [tailwind.config.js](mdc:tailwind.config.js)

### Component-Specific SCSS
- Form styles: [src/scss/components/_form.scss](mdc:src/scss/components/_form.scss)
- Button styles: [src/scss/components/_buttons.scss](mdc:src/scss/components/_buttons.scss)
- Navigation: [src/scss/components/_form-nav.scss](mdc:src/scss/components/_form-nav.scss)

## Styling Conventions

### Class Naming
Use BEM methodology for custom classes:
```scss
.form-step {
  // Block
  
  &__header {
    // Element
  }
  
  &--active {
    // Modifier
  }
}
```

### Tailwind First Approach
1. **Primary**: Use Tailwind utility classes for layout and common styling
2. **Secondary**: Create custom SCSS for complex components
3. **Custom Properties**: Use CSS custom properties for theming

### Component Structure
```scss
// Component: _component-name.scss
.component-name {
  // Base styles
  
  // Responsive breakpoints
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    // Tablet styles
  }
  
  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    // Desktop styles
  }
  
  // State variations
  &.is-active {
    // Active state
  }
  
  // Nested elements
  .sub-element {
    // Nested styles
  }
}
```

## Font Management
Custom fonts are located in [src/app/fonts/](mdc:src/app/fonts/):
- Use font-face declarations from [src/app/fonts/stylesheet.css](mdc:src/app/fonts/stylesheet.css)
- Follow the established font family hierarchy

## Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach
- Use consistent breakpoints aligned with Tailwind
- Test across all supported devices

## Color System
- Define color variables in main SCSS files
- Use consistent naming conventions
- Maintain accessibility contrast ratios

## Performance Considerations
- Minimize custom CSS where Tailwind suffices
- Use SCSS nesting judiciously (max 3 levels deep)
- Organize imports efficiently in main.scss
